                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Brenlo wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Okey doke folks,</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
How I read this: "Bah, you're over-reacting and I don't have time for this."
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Brenlo wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">We feel that charm as it stood when used in pre-omens content had a disparity in its risk vs. reward.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
How I read this: Enough others complained to us that you were too uber that we decided to nerf you. We did not take into account the number of character-related resources (i.e. snare, stuns, bard mez, another slower, another puller, your own healer, etc.) it takes to charm at this level because, well, neither did the people complaining. 
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Brenlo wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Rather than adjust charm overall to reduce the amount of damage all charmed pets do even more, we made changes to the NPCs in the new zones only.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
How I read this: "We have made up our mind and there is nothing you can do to change it. Sit down and shut up or we will nerf you in the old world too."
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Brenlo wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">We also made more NPCs overall charmable to provide more variety and fun for the enchanter.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
How I read this: By "more NPCs overall" I am refering only to those mobs in the new zones. See above.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Brenlo wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">This is not a nerf.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
How I read this: Brenlo, thinking - "Talking points work so well for politicians maybe they will for us too. After all it's not the enchanters we have to convince, just the majority of the other classes." Brenlo, aloud to enchanters "Don't even try to fight us on this." Brenlo, aloud to the other classes "And don't let those whiney enchanters tell you they are being nerfed. This is clearly just a fix. When you see dozens of them LFG on the sidelines in the future, don't you worry. They are balanced now. Oh, and don't feel guilty asking them for buffs. Utiilities, after all, are what define the enchanter character. In a way, they exist to C you. Don't be afraid to ask.. nay demand they utilize these 'utilities.'"
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Brenlo wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The way charm works has not been changed one bit.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
How I read this: "We are standing by all past 'changes' to charm as well. Charm will continue to take upto 33% of the group's xp [the equivalent of upto 2.5 PCs under the current xp system], the rule of 4 will stay in effect and the risk associated with charm will remain the same. Also, despite this 'change,' charm remains a viable and powerful tool for the enchanter class. Now that charm is fixed, enchanters are 'balanced' with other classes. Nothing needs to be done to compensate for this change, especially given all the powerful 'utilities' or 'buffs' the enchanter class posesses. We will be leaving all three OoW charm spells in place. There will be no re-assessment of enchanter needs at this time."
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Brenlo wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The way the new NPCs react when charmed has been modified so that we no longer have issues of charmed mobs doing the DPS of several rogues.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
How I read this: Brenlo, to mages rogues wizards and other DPS classes, "See?! We are listening to you! We nerfed enchanters for you." Brenlo, to enchanters, "We have been getting too many complaints from other classes about your ability to charm. We have not actually investigated these nor have we taken into account what is actually involved in charming [snarer, healer, stunner, additional slower, additional puller, rezzer, etc.] but have decided to appease the other DPS classes anyway. Oh, bytheway, you are no longer considered a DPS class at all. Enchanters will now be refered to solely as a 'utility' class or, alternatively, merely as 'slow.'"</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=361216" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ariu <span style="font-style: italic">stop destroying my class damnit!</span> Vil''''Aki &lt;Heroes&gt;</a>
