When?
<br />
Why?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">One should also keep in mind that the last two nerfs to hit other classes HAVE been discussed by SoE with the affected classes.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
~~ waves hands ~~
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">This is not a nerf.</span>
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Slay undead was reversed within a week</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
They had the courtisy of telling paladins about the slay undead change before they pushed it live.  It never made it live.
<br />

<br />
This didn't happen for enchanters.  The only ones who knew about it communicated a half-true relay of what it was 2 days before it went live, no information directly from the developers or announcement was made.  "This is not a nerf" is the only developer statement I've seen on the subject.
<br />

<br />
Strangely, the slay undead 'nerf' would have made paladins a better, if different, class.  They would have been top-end DPS (or tanking) for any undead targets, not both: now they are tanking with mediocre DPS on undead targets.
<br />

<br />
(that is, if you actually read the SOE dev's description of their change, and believed it -- many people didn't)
<br />

<br />
The reaction against it was based off (if I remember correctly) the presumption of Luclin-era soloing, not off of group utility.
<br />

<br />
The charm nerf guts the ability.  An ability they had already gutted in the entire high end of GoD, and where everything is still flagged no charm.  If enchanter's didn't object to having no charm in GoD, how could they object to having a gimped charm in OoW?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
